23/08/2009
ATHENS, Greece -- The government declared a state of emergency on Saturday (August 22nd) after a big forest fire spread in the region of Athens.
The fire-damaged dozens of houses were and prompted the evacuation of three villages.
It broke out late on Friday in the village of Grammatiko, 40km northeast of the capital, but fire fighters were unable to contain it due to strong winds.
The government requested help from Cyprus, Italy and France, and they are expected to provide support on Sunday.
Other fires continued to burn on the central Aegean islands of Skyros and Evia and the Ionian island of Zakynthos.
(AFP - 23/08/09;
Reuters, AFP, Sky, CNN - 22/08/09)
